The mutineers<br />
The document to be prepared is about an adventure story that was adapted both in books<br />
and in films. Your task is to create the document based on the description and the example<br />
using files zendulok.txt and hajo.jpg .<br />
1. Open the source text zendulok.txt (its coding is ISO8859-2) and save it as sziget in<br />
the default format of the word processor.<br />
2. The source text contains text input errors: redundant spaces, tabs and paragraph marks.<br />
Correct and delete these.<br />
3. The page layout should be landscape.<br />
4. The text should be arranged on the page using a table.<br />
a. The table has three columns but merge or split the cells where it is necessary.<br />
b. Determine the number of rows based on the example.<br />
c. The external border of the table should be a thin line.<br />
d. Place the text parts into the cells according to the example.<br />
e. The font type of the text is Times New Roman or Nimbus Roman and the font<br />
size is 12 points.<br />
5. The title, “The secret island of the mutineers” should appear in the middle. Its font size is<br />
26 points, its style is bold, the spacing before and after it is 12 points (0.42 cm).<br />
6. Add a footnote mark at the end of the title with symbol “*”. Type in the text of the foot-<br />
note.<br />
7. The format of the text in the first and third columns is<br />
a. the left and right indents are 0.2 cm;<br />
b. the indent of the first line is 0.5 cm;<br />
c. the paragraphs are justified.<br />
8. Insert picture hajo.jpg into the second column; align it centered horizontally. Display a<br />
border of width 4 to 5 points above and below it for the whole width of the column. The<br />
distance between the lines and the picture should be exactly 0.2 cm. Do not use excess<br />
paragraph marks for the arrangement.<br />
9. The caption should be 12 points below the bottom border; it should be aligned centered<br />
and its font style should be italics.<br />
10. Use hyphenation in the document where it is required.<br />
11. Create the header according to the example. Type in the text and align it right. Insert a thin<br />
line above and below it for the whole width of the page.<br /></p>
